Video 14 — Break and Continue

Overview:
Control loop execution: break exits the loop, continue skips to the next iteration.

Key Concepts:

Optimize loop execution
Useful for early exit or conditional skipping

Example:

for i in range(5):
    if i == 3:
        break
    if i == 1:
        continue
    print(i)

Practical Insights:

Reduces unnecessary computation
Improves efficiency in iterative tasks
